post_text: One of our very own #OnHolton students received a very special invitation from First Lady Melania Trump to attend the opening of a new student art exhibit honoring the women's suffrage movement and the 19th amendment. Joy Barnard, a Holton Middle School student, was selected as the Michigan representative for the "Building the Movement" art exhibit. Joy had the opportunity to meet Mrs. Trump, several other cabinet officials, and other student artists from across the country. Joy was joined by her twin sister Martha and their parents on this memorable visit to Washington, D.C. You can learn more about the exhibit and view Joy's art work by visiting https://www.womensvote100.org/buildingthemovement. What an incredible experience! Way to go Joy! On Holton!

post_text:
Dear Holton Families:

The US 2020 Census will be finishing soon. I strongly encourage all of our families to complete the census and be counted! The 2020 Census count impacts the federal funds that communities receive each year for programs and services that are critical for schools, students, and younger children, such as:

Special education, Head Start, after-school programs, and classroom technology.

Food assistance, including free and reduced-price school lunches.

Maternal and child health programs.

So far, our community has done a great job completing the census! Holton, Cedar Creek, Blue Lake, Bridgeton, and Greenwood townships currently have over 68% who have completed the census. In 2010, we had approximately a 73% response rate. Help bring the response rates to above 75% or higher! Visit 2020CENSUS.GOV to complete the census.

With Great Respect,
Dr. Bayne

post_text:
Class of 2021 Scholarship Opportunity!!

College Board runs an annual College Board Opportunity Scholarship (CBOS). Seniors have the opportunity to be eligible for a $40,000 scholarship and the process to do it is pretty easy. In addition to the $40,000 scholarships, if students complete one of six steps they receive an entry for smaller scholarships (winners drawn monthly).

In order to have a chance for the $40,000 “Complete Your Journey” scholarship, seniors must build their college list in their College Board account by using BigFuture and they need to complete this step by July 31st. If they complete this step they receive an entry for a $500 scholarship.

post_text:
The Michigan College Access Network has recently launched a new College Advising Hotline. Students and their families can call or text the hotline with questions about financial aid, FAFSA, registering for college, applying to college, trade schools, and much more! Students will receive answers to their questions along with resources, and be connected with who or what they need to succeed.

This hotline is free for all Michigan high school students and their families, and will continue throughout the summer. Holton students that contact the hotline will be put in touch with our College Adviser, Ms. Smalec.

College Advising Hotline: (810) 373-5385 (call or text)

Walked out of my house this morning to find this❤️ I am seriously in awe of Holton public schools and the amazing staff that works there!! I am SO very proud to be a part of your community and district ❤️ You treat everyone equally special. I started there almost 10 years ago with enviroclean and I felt like family from day one ❤️ On behalf of myself and my employees thank you all from the bottom of our hearts. I can tell you I feltl totally special that you thought of us as well in your sign delivery 😊 I think we are all Superheros in some way, shape or form. That's why I posted the Hero picture also.
Ms. Melissa misses everyone big or small. Can't wait to see everyone again. Stay safe and be well❤️

We are incredibly thankful for the amazing food service staff at Holton Public Schools!

post_text: #OnHolton is always ready to support the community during times of need. Yesterday, our team delivered food and instructional materials to nearly every student in the district. Also, we are nearly ready to begin distributing Chromebooks to those without devices. It isn't surprising how our community rallies together to help each other, but this impressive feat is a great reason to be proud! #SchoolsGetItDone

post_text: Hi, please read this message carefully about pickup for our Chromebook borrowing plan for those of you that had signed up prior to this posting. We will be distributing them Thursday, 4-23 and Friday 4-24 from 12 to 2pm at the District Service Building. Grades 4th – 8th only please. We will have a plan next week for K-3 that need to borrow something. Please follow the arrows around the parking lot and pull up to walkway. Someone will come out and ask for your student’s name and address and relay it to a team member and bring out to you. You must have signed up and agreed to terms on the form for you to receive one prior to this posting. If you requested a replacement charging cable, please bring your Chromebook so we know what charging cable you need. If you sign up after this posting your Chromebook will be scheduled for a pickup next week TBA. Thank You!

post_text: Greetings Holton Families! Holton Public Schools have completed our Remote Learning Plan. It is now posted to our website. Specific details about your child's learning will be shared by building principals and teachers. We plan to implement our plan on Monday, April 20 and will provide support for the remainder of the school year. It may be necessary to modify our plan as we move forward. We will work hard to keep everyone as informed as possible of those changes. More than anything, we want to help support our families to be safe and well during this time. Our teachers are eager to check in on our students and engage them in learning! Should you have any questions, contact Mr. Carlson or Mrs. Byrnes. Stay safe and healthy!
text: Greetings Holton Families! Holton Public Schools have completed our Remote Learning Plan. It is now posted to our website. Specific details about your child's learning will be shared by building principals and teachers. We plan to implement our plan on Monday, April 20 and will provide support for the remainder of the school year. It may be necessary to modify our plan as we move forward. We will work hard to keep everyone as informed as possible of those changes. More than anything, we want to help support our families to be safe and well during this time. Our teachers are eager to check in on our students and engage them in learning! Should you have any questions, contact Mr. Carlson or Mrs. Byrnes. Stay safe and healthy!

Zoinks! It's the last day of March is Reading Month, Holton Heroes! We're celebrating 31 days, thousands of pages, and millions of words read by getting all fancy on Dress to Impress Day. Make today special, get spiffy with me, and READ, READ, READ!
No matter what happens or how long we're apart, Mr. Follett and all of your other teachers and friends at Holton Public Schools are thinking of you, missing you like crazy, and counting the days until we get to see you again. Stay safe and healthy. See you soon!

The letter details the several items/funds we still need to have donated to build our class' Snowcoming Mini-Float (fits in a red toy wagon!), which is due to be presented this Friday.

Thank you in advance!

--Andrew Haak & Dana Burkett

post_text:
Mr. Haak's 7th Grade Social Studies classes have been studying Ancient Egypt and recently had a chance to *taste* history! Mr. Haak's lesson blended STEM (Science, Technology, Engineering, & Math) into Social Studies as students compared the Nile River & Great Lakes watersheds. The kids learned that Ancient Egyptians loved sweets, just like we do, and would use the Nile River to grow dates, figs, and other fruits to flavor their breads and food.

As a follow-up, Mr. Haak brought in some whole dried figs and chopped dates for an Ancient Egypt Taste Test. Most of the kids were brave and tried both, and many were surprised to find that they really liked the taste! Many even took seconds! It was just one way to make that connection to historical events a little more memorable (and delicious)!

post_text:
Attention Senior Families: The FAFSA Deadline is quickly approaching! The FAFSA (Free Application for Federal Student Aid) is a federal document that students need to complete by March 1st in order to receive financial aid for college.

Students that complete their FAFSA will automatically be awarded a $5 Wesco gift card, and entered in a raffle to win even more prizes!

You can start the form at fafsa.gov. Please contact Hayley Smalec, our college adviser, by email (hsmalec@holton.k12.mi.us) or phone (821-1916) for assistance in completing the form.

post_text: Last week, our seniors had a busy week! They attended presentations about FAFSA (Free Application for Federal Student Aid), establishing credit and loan borrowing, scholarships, resume and interview tips, and were able to speak from different employers throughout West Michigan. We would like to thank representatives from Gerber Federal Credit Union, West Michigan Works, Scherdel, Spectrum Health, ADAC Automotive, Healthwest, Steamfitters and Pipefitters Union, the Department of Natural Resources, and the 2020 Census for coming and speaking to our students!
